====The following parts are confirmed to be compatible with the Cr-48:==== 
==== ==== 
==LCD Panel== 
* Original LCD panel is Samsung model [[http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00APMM4RA/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B00APMM4RA&linkCode=as2&tag=mcdotechserv-20|LTN121AT10]]

==AC Adapters[[image:cr48parts.jpg align="right"]]== 
* Original AC adapter is manufactured by Lite On Technology (Changzhou) Co., Ltd.
** Model: PA-1400-20GI
** Input: 100-240V ~1.0A 50-60Hz
** Output: 19.5V 2.05A
* [[http://amzn.to/1kE1kGQ|Hewlett-Packard NA374AA#ABA Mini 30W AC Adapter]]
* [[http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003NJUPQE/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B003NJUPQE&linkCode=as2&tag=mcdotechserv-20|Lenmar 50-Watt Notebook Power Adapter Lac50]] (<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Adjustable output voltage: 9.5V to 20V. Set to 19.5V for Cr-48)</span>
* <span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">[[@http://www.finsix.com|FINsix DART Adapter]] ('A' tip w/4.0x1.7mm DC Male to 5.5x2.1mm DC Female HP adapter OR 'G' tip)</span>
==Battery== 
* Currently no known source for compatible replacement battery
* Original 63Wh lithium-ion battery manufactured by Hewlett-Packard
* Specifications:
** rechargeable: yes
** energy-empty: 0 Wh
** energy-full: 62.6632 Wh
** energy-full-design: 62.5152 Wh
** energy-rate: 9.4868 W
** voltage: 15.255 V
** technology: lithium-ion
* [[file:cr48_battery_1.jpg|Battery teardown photo 1]]
* [[file:cr48_battery_2.jpg|Battery teardown photo 2]]
